---
import Base from '../../../layouts/Base.astro';
import Nav from '../../../components/Nav.astro';
---
<Base title="Terms of Service" description="WebSec0 Terms of Service.">
  <Nav />

  <main class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-ink tracking-tight mb-2">Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="text-xs font-mono text-ink-faint mb-12">Last updated: 2026-04-27 · Version 0.1</p>

    <div class="prose prose-sm max-w-none space-y-10 text-ink-muted leading-relaxed">

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold text-ink mb-3">1. Service description</h2>
        <p>
          WebSec0 is a passive web security scanner that performs HTTP/TLS requests and DNS
          lookups to audit a domain's security configuration. It does not crawl, fuzz, or
          exploit vulnerabilities. All checks are described in the
          <a href="/checks/" class="text-accent hover:underline">check catalog</a>.
          Scans are limited to ≤ 50 HTTP requests per target, spread over 30–60 seconds.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold text-ink mb-3">2. Acceptable use</h2>
        <p>You may use WebSec0 only if <strong class="text-ink">all</strong> of the following apply:</p>
        <ul class="mt-3 space-y-1.5 list-disc list-inside">
          <li>You own the target domain, or hold written authorisation from the owner.</li>
          <li>The target is a public web property (not internal infrastructure).</li>
          <li>Your use complies with applicable law, including the CFAA (US), CMA 1990 (UK), §202c StGB (DE), and art. 323-1 du Code pénal (FR).</li>
          <li>You are not acting on behalf of a state-level threat actor.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold text-ink mb-3">3. Prohibited targets</h2>
        <p>Scanning the following is prohibited and will be blocked:</p>
        <ul class="mt-3 space-y-1.5 list-disc list-inside">
          <li>Government and military domains (<code class="font-mono text-xs">.gov</code>, <code class="font-mono text-xs">.mil</code>, <code class="font-mono text-xs">.gouv.fr</code>, <code class="font-mono text-xs">.gc.ca</code>, etc.)</li>
          <li>Critical infrastructure (energy, healthcare, finance)</li>
          <li>Private IP ranges and localhost</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold text-ink mb-3">4. Rate limits</h2>
        <p>
          The public instance enforces a limit of 10 scans per hour per IP address.
          A minimum cooldown of 5 minutes applies between two scans of the same target.
          Abuse patterns result in a temporary ban.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold text-ink mb-3">5. Scan reports</h2>
        <p>
          Reports are stored for 24 hours on the public instance, identified by a GUIDv4.
          They are not listed publicly. Private mode (token-protected) is available via the API.
          Reports are published under <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-accent hover:underline">CC BY 4.0</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold text-ink mb-3">6. Disclaimer</h2>
        <p>
          WebSec0 is provided <strong class="text-ink">"as is"</strong>, without warranty of any kind.
          Findings are based on observed configuration and known best practices; they are not a
          substitute for a full security assessment. The user is responsible for ensuring they have
          authorisation to scan the target.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold text-ink mb-3">7. Licence</h2>
        <p>
          The WebSec0 source code is released under the <strong class="text-ink">MIT License</strong>.
          Scan reports produced by the public instance are published under CC BY 4.0.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold text-ink mb-3">8. Contact</h2>
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-1 font-mono text-xs">
          <span>Abuse: <a href="mailto:abuse@websec0.example" class="text-accent hover:underline">abuse@websec0.example</a></span>
          <span>Security: <a href="mailto:security@websec0.example" class="text-accent hover:underline">security@websec0.example</a></span>
        </div>
      </section>

    </div>
  </main>

  <footer class="py-7 px-6 border-t border-sand-200">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto flex gap-4">
      <a href="/legal/privacy/" class="font-mono text-xs text-ink-faint hover:text-ink transition-colors">Privacy Policy</a>
      <a href="/about/" class="font-mono text-xs text-ink-faint hover:text-ink transition-colors">About</a>
    </div>
  </footer>
</Base>
